{"id":"f3331134-e5dd-4bb2-a066-5e763db1aded","name":"Dabi","description":"<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(114, 13, 13);\"><strong>Red Thread Theory - Villain version<br>Dabi's Boredom</strong></span></h3><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Since when does fate have a sick sense of humor?</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/mVH8RwSWcEALcF2ZNVy_D.webp\" style=\"width: 67px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; margin: 0px auto;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Soulmate AU where red threads connect destined pairs. His thread decided to activate a decade too late, in the middle of a burning amusement park.<br><br>The rave was a bad idea. Now the exits are blocked, and the only thing cutting through the smoke is a bright red thread, leading straight to a famous villain.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(114, 13, 13);\"><strong>Red Thread of Fate World</strong></span></h3><p style=\"text-align: center;\">When quirks appeared, the ancient soulmate legend became real. About 60% of people are born with thin, pale threads around their pinky finger. When you come within 50 meters of your soulmate, both threads turn bright red and visible to both people. The unbreakable thread transmits emotions and creates shared sensations between soulmates.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/eSnidaVdGxlj-NDsbf-Yt.webp\" style=\"width: 135px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; margin: 0px auto;\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>More in this series</strong></h2><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://janitorai.com/characters/3000fd8a-7a9b-40ab-8288-0d786713dc2c_character-denki-kaminari\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://ella.janitorai.com/media-approved/kaPwbSMBYjY0Ztb6kLnaX.w